Denn against Mc. Donald.

Note. See 1 Richards. C. P. 115. Green v. Gauntlet 1 Str. 531. 1 Sellon v. Prac. 408. 2 Tidd’s Pr. 696. 3 East. 1.

A notice of trial and countermand is such a proceeding within the year, as supersedes the necessity for a term’s notice of tris!.

IN ejectment. In this cause it was held ^ that a notice of trial and countermand within the year, was such a proceeding as to supersede the necessity for a term’s notice of trial, (a)
